{% comment %}
  Reusable monochrome (1-bit-friendly) weather icons for TRMNL/Terminus.

  Terminus's editor has no Liquid partials, so this is a copy-paste block:
  paste the STYLE + CAPTURE DEFINITIONS section ONCE near the top of your
  template's content, then use the SELECTOR snippet wherever you want an icon.

  Icons are solid FILLED glyphs built from ONLY <path> (filled discs are drawn
  as arc paths too — the device mis-positions <circle>, and drops strokes /
  fill=none / transforms entirely). The <style> just controls size. Default
  40px; wrap in `.wx-lg` for the large variant.

  Driven by Home Assistant's standard `condition` strings (which the WeatherFlow
  Forecast integration emits): sunny, clear-night, partlycloudy, cloudy, fog,
  rainy, pouring, hail, snowy, snowy-rainy, lightning, lightning-rainy, windy,
  windy-variant, exceptional.
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %} ============ STYLE + CAPTURE DEFINITIONS (paste once) ============ {% endcomment %}
<style>
  .wx-icon { display: block; width: 40px; height: 40px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .wx-lg .wx-icon { width: 88px; height: 88px; }
</style>

